117
00:04:52,630 --> 00:04:55,120
Which has been around for
a while, but no one really

118
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:58,390
got around to implementing
it until really recent years.

119
00:04:58,390 --> 00:05:01,950
At least on any kind of scale, with
big companies like Google and Comcast

120
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:06,400
and the like finally starting to give
people not just 32-bit addresses,

