when it is sending data from point A

451
00:20:12,730 --> 00:20:18,640
to some other point B, if that other
computer is on the same local network

452
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:21,260
or if it's elsewhere on the internet.

453
00:20:21,260 --> 00:20:25,980
And so essentially this
subnet mask, 255.255.240.0,

454
00:20:25,980 --> 00:20:28,200
represents a pattern of ones and zeros.

455
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:32,260
It uses that patterns of ones
and zeros to determine, hm,

456
00:20:32,260 --> 00:20:35,710
I am trying to request or send
information to this other server.

457
00:20:35,710 --> 00:20:39,040
If that pattern of one
and zeros tells my Mac

458
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:42,030
that, ooh, that other computer is
